HR Analytics Dashboard (Power BI)

Project Overview

This project analyzes employee data to understand workforce trends, employee attrition, job satisfaction, and demographic patterns using Power BI.

Tools Used

- Power BI
- Power Query
- DAX
- Data Cleaning
- Data Visualization

Dashboard Features

- Overall Employee Count
- Employee Attrition Analysis
- Attrition Rate Calculation
- Active Employee Analysis
- Average Age Analysis
- Department-wise Attrition
- Education Field-wise Attrition
- Job Satisfaction Rating Analysis
- Age Group and Gender Analysis

Key Insights

- The overall attrition rate is 17.31%.
- The Research & Development department has the highest employee count.
- Employees aged 25–34 show higher attrition compared to other age groups.
- Job satisfaction levels vary across different job roles.
- Education background influences employee attrition patterns.

Business Value

This dashboard helps HR teams:

- Monitor employee turnover.
- Identify high-risk employee groups.
- Improve employee retention strategies.
- Analyze workforce demographics and satisfaction.

